# Home Network Security
# Ignore sensitive inventory files and backups

# Nmap XMLs, device inventories, and any scans containing real MAC addresses, host details, live IPs, etc.
# These are stored locally in docs/inventory/ but should not be committed to git.
*.xml

# Draw.io backup / autosave files (may embed sensitive diagram details)
*.drawio.bak
*.drawio~
*.bak.drawio

# Other sensitive files and secrets
*.key
*.pem
id_rsa*
*.env
.env.*
secrets/
credentials/
*.passwd
passwords*.txt

# OS and editor artifacts
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# To force include a sanitized inventory despite the rule:
#   git add -f docs/inventory/sanitized-devices.xml
# Or prefer non-sensitive formats like devices.md or devices.csv in docs/inventory/
